		"userdoc": {
			"kind": "user",
			"methods": {
				"getWinner()": {
					"notice": "View who won"
				},
				"joinGame(uint256)": {
					"notice": "Join the game as Player 1 (index 0) or Player 2 (index 1)"
				},
				"resetGame()": {
					"notice": "Reset the game for a new round (only owner)"
				},
				"rollDice()": {
					"notice": "Anyone can trigger the roll once both answers are in         Uses exactly what you asked: length of both answers → mod 6 + 1"
				},
				"setQuestion(string)": {
					"notice": "Owner sets a simple question to ask the players"
				},
				"submitAnswer(string)": {
					"notice": "Submit your answer to the question (any string – length will decide the roll!)"
				}
			},
			"notice": "A fun 2-player on-chain game:   1. Owner sets a simple question (e.g. \"What is your favorite movie?\" or \"Describe your dream vacation in one sentence\")   2. Two players join (Player 1 = index 0, Player 2 = index 1)   3. Both players submit their answers (any string they want – the length is what matters!)   4. Anyone calls rollDice() → (lengthOfAnswer1 + lengthOfAnswer2) % 6 + 1   5. Result is a \"dice roll\" from 1 to 6:      - 1, 2 or 3 → Player 1 wins      - 4, 5 or 6 → Player 2 wins   The game is deliberately simple so you can deploy it instantly and play with friends.   Note: In a real dApp the frontend would display the question and let players type answers.         On-chain, the second player can see the first player's answer length, so for fairness         you can add commit-reveal later (I kept it simple as per your request).",
